# ERP Dashboard UI Skill

## 🎯 Design Goal

Create a **clean, professional, modern dashboard UI** similar to CRM/ERP systems with:

- Left sidebar navigation
- Top header bar
- Data tables with actions
- Cards and stats
- Forms with proper spacing
- Soft colors and minimal design

---

## 🧠 When to use this skill

- ERP system UI
- Hospital management dashboard
- CRM contact list
- Admin panel
- Project management UI
- SaaS dashboard

---

## 🧱 Layout Structure

### 1. Main Layout

- Sidebar (fixed left)
- Top navbar (search + profile)
- Content area (right)

```txt
| Sidebar | Topbar |
| Sidebar | Content |
2. Sidebar Design
Width: 240px
Background: dark (#0f172a or similar)
Text: light
Active item: highlighted with background
Icons + labels

Menu Example:

Dashboard
Contacts
Projects
Reports
Settings
3. Topbar
Search input (rounded)
Right side:
Notifications
User avatar
Height: ~60px
Background: white
📊 Table Design (IMPORTANT)

Follow clean table UI like image:

Row height: 56px+
Padding: px-4 py-3
Light borders (border-gray-200)
Hover effect: bg-gray-50
Rounded container

Columns:

Checkbox
Name (with avatar)
Status (badge)
Owner (avatar group)
Actions (dropdown)
🧾 Form Design (Modal Style)
Use modal or card
Input spacing: mb-4
Label above input
Rounded inputs
Soft borders

Fields example:

Name
Date
Dropdown
Budget
Description

Buttons:

Primary: blue
Secondary: gray
🎨 Design System
Colors
Primary: Blue (#2563eb)
Background: #f8fafc
Card: white
Border: #e5e7eb
Spacing
Section padding: p-6
Card padding: p-4
Gap: gap-4 or gap-6
Typography
Title: text-xl font-semibold
Label: text-sm text-gray-600
Body: text-sm
🧩 Components to Generate

Always include:

Sidebar component
Header component
Table component
Card component
Modal form
Button variants
⚡ UX Best Practices
Keep UI minimal (no clutter)
Use consistent spacing
Align everything properly
Use icons for clarity
Avoid heavy colors
Use shadows lightly
📱 Responsiveness
Sidebar collapses on mobile
Table scrolls horizontally
Stack cards on small screens
🚀 Output Expectation

When generating code:

Use Next.js + Tailwind
Create reusable components
Keep code clean and modular
Follow modern SaaS UI patterns
